#Git Hub

#Git clone 

To clone repo ====> git clone githublink


#Branch commands

To create new branch =====> git checkout -b branchname
To go to other branch =====> git checkout branchname

If you have pre existing project:
create a repo
git init
git remote ...

#ACP

git add . --------> adding branch
git commit -u "Message" -------> commiting message
git push -u origin branch -----> pushing branch


#Pull ------> getting codes
git pull origin branchname


#Fetch ------> getting update
git fetch

#Status -----> getting info about which branch
git status


#After changing some code you will have 3 decission: 
Decission 1 : you dont want the current changes leave it =====> git stash / git reset --hard
Decission 2 : you might new this code for future use ======> git checkout -b tempbranch and then ACP
Decission 3 : this changes are must code ======> ACP